    <summary><span data-ttu-id="75410-101">定义确定年份第一周的不同规则。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="75410-101">Defines different rules for determining the first week of the year.</span></span></summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="75410-102">由 <xref:System.Globalization.CalendarWeekRule> 属性返回并由区域性的当前日历用来确定日历周规则的 <xref:System.Globalization.DateTimeFormatInfo.CalendarWeekRule%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> 枚举的成员。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="75410-102">A member of the <xref:System.Globalization.CalendarWeekRule> enumeration is returned by the <xref:System.Globalization.DateTimeFormatInfo.CalendarWeekRule%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> property and is used by the culture's current calendar to determine the calendar week rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="75410-103">枚举值还用作 <xref:System.Globalization.Calendar.GetWeekOfYear%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> 方法的参数。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="75410-103">The enumeration value is also used as a parameter to the <xref:System.Globalization.Calendar.GetWeekOfYear%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="75410-104">日历周规则取决于表示一周的第一天的 <xref:System.DayOfWeek?displayProperty=nameWithType> 值以及 <xref:System.Globalization.CalendarWeekRule> 值。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="75410-104">Calendar week rules depend on the <xref:System.DayOfWeek?displayProperty=nameWithType> value that indicates the first day of the week in addition to depending on a <xref:System.Globalization.CalendarWeekRule> value.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="75410-105"><xref:System.Globalization.DateTimeFormatInfo.FirstDayOfWeek%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>属性的默认值为提供一种文化，但任何<xref:System.DayOfWeek>可以将值指定为中的周中的第一天<xref:System.Globalization.Calendar.GetWeekOfYear%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>方法。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="75410-105">The <xref:System.Globalization.DateTimeFormatInfo.FirstDayOfWeek%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> property provides the default value for a culture, but any <xref:System.DayOfWeek> value can be specified as the first day of the week in the <xref:System.Globalization.Calendar.GetWeekOfYear%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="75410-106">基于 FirstDay 值的第一周可以有 1 到 7 天。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="75410-106">The first week based on the FirstDay value can have one to seven days.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="75410-107">始终根据 FirstFullWeek 值的第一周为七天。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="75410-107">The first week based on the FirstFullWeek value always has seven days.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="75410-108">基于 FirstFourDayWeek 值的第一周可以有四到七天。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="75410-108">The first week based on the FirstFourDayWeek value can have four to seven days.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="75410-109">例如，在公历日历中，假设一年 (1 月 1 日) 的第一天是星期二和一周的指定第一天是星期日。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="75410-109">For example, in the Gregorian calendar, suppose that the first day of the year (January 1) falls on a Tuesday and the designated first day of the week is Sunday.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="75410-110">选择 FirstFullWeek 定义为一年的第一周开始的第一个星期日 (1 月 6 日)。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="75410-110">Selecting FirstFullWeek defines the first Sunday (January 6) as the beginning of the first week of the year.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="75410-111">一年中的前五天被视为上一年的最后一周的一部分。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="75410-111">The first five days of the year are considered part of the last week of the previous year.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="75410-112">与此相反，选择 FirstFourDayWeek 定义年 (1 月 1 日) 的第一天为一年的第一周的开头因为有多个四天从 1 月 1 日到以下的前一天星期日。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="75410-112">In contrast, selecting FirstFourDayWeek defines the first day of the year (January 1) as the beginning of the first week of the year because there are more than four days from January 1 to the day before the following Sunday.</span></span>  
  
